
This software only runs on modern versions of linux.  It makes
extensive use of non-portable file system namespace facilities.

To get the software, run:

    git clone github.com:stanford-scs/jai.git
    cd jai

To build the software, run:

    make

To install it, run one of the following:

    # To install in the default location of /usr/local/bin
    make && sudo make install

    # To override the default location and install in /usr
    make && make install PREFIX=/usr

    # To package the files
    fakeroot sh -c 'make install DESTDIR=pkg PREFIX=/usr && \
                    tar -czf jai.`uname -m`.tgz -C pkg .'
